    "description": "An Early Byzantine fortification in the Liguria Maritima.",
    "details": "\r\n<p>A hilltop settlement, with occupation in the Late Bronze Age, then abandoned and built as a fortress during the Byzantine rule of Liguria (mid 6th-mid7th CE). It is slightly inland, probably meant more as a watchtower against military actions from the North, as is the case for Filattiera, further East.</p>\r\n<p>In the Middle Ages a church was built on the hilltop site.</p>\r\n",
